com.continuent.tungsten.fsm.event
Class EventDispatcherTask

java.lang.Object
  com.continuent.tungsten.fsm.event.EventDispatcherTask
All Implemented Interfaces:
EventDispatcher, java.lang.Runnable
public class EventDispatcherTask
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable, EventDispatcher

This class defines an event dispatcher task, which is a separate thread that dispatches events to a listener from a queue. It handles normal events, out-of-band events, and event cancellation.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Teemu Ollakka, Robert Hodges

put

public EventRequest put(Event event)
                 throws java.lang.InterruptedException
Puts an event in the queue for normal processing. This method returns a Future that callers can call to obtain the event status. Events that implement the {#link OutOfBandEvent} interface will be dispatched as if the user had called putOutOfBand(Event).
